(1, 'PROFESSION BASED COWORKING SPACE: IS IT THE FUTURE', '1.jpg', '\r\n			          <div class=\"post-content color-text-a\">\r\n            <p class=\"post-intro\">\r\n            \"There\'s a refreshing wave of shared space for running operations that\'s serving the wants of service based professionals and their clients. We\'re talking regarding profession based co-working; and doctors, lawyers, tutors, health professionals seem to be quite intrigued by this new conception.\"\r\n            </p>\r\n\r\n            <p>\r\n            Traditionally, professionals rent workplace area to serve the wants of their personal practices. However, over the past few years, the field has seen abundant consolidation of personal practices with areas being shared & integrated for larger scale operations and growth.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n\r\n            The reason behind this consolidation is far just like the rapidly increasing co-working. Professions in operation don\'t own offices, even if they do they become larger suppliers to aggregate space so as to reap the advantages that result in higher footfall, more people coming in. Auxiliary business generated becomes much larger from the shared space and new gentry coming in to get consultation.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            This generates an oversized quantity of savings as a result of shared area conjointly suggests that shared resources (meaning access to resources at a lower price equipped by larger space by coaching centres, chambers & gyms providers). It\'s definitely a huge saving as compared to average rent for professionals vis-a-vis a case where there are multiple individual coaching centres, clinics or gyms.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n\r\n            Dr Rashmi, consultant in the dermatologist department of a reputed corporate hospital shares the insight \"practitioners preferring to not share can find themselves having a troublesome time competing with the big space aggregators,\" during a recent conversation.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            \"If customers have gotten comfy sharing automobile rides and flats, then physicians will get comfy sharing their OPD\'s with a number of their contemporaries\" she added.\r\n\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            \"It really comes down to how the space, services, and pricing are designed and what their other alternatives are,\" explains management of a space provider for teachers on the ideal location on Sohna Road, Gurgaon. He says tutors save plenty of cash on direct capital expenses and current monthly overhead if they\'re willing to create some tweaks in their thinking,\" he added.\r\n\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            Consistent with the flexibility and convenience that general coworking areas give, Profrea offers tenants the power to book and access these profession based shared area for the brief amounts of time. Professionals are empowered to break the lease into hourly bases. Space owners can generate more revenue from their assets as it\'s only being occupied for some days every week by them. Simply, search for profession based shared space for rent near you on Profrea.\r\n            </p>\r\n          </div>\r\n', 'Doctors', 'Pradeep', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2020-05-02 06:24:30', '2020-05-02 06:24:30'),
(2, 'FOUR FACTORS TO KEEP IN MIND TO FINALIZE SPACE FOR SERVICE BASED PROFESSIONALS', '1.jpg', '\r\n			\r\n          <div class=\"post-content color-text-a\">\r\n            <p class=\"post-intro\">\r\n            \"It is scary for a brand new medical or healthcare workspaces or coaching centres. Not to mention the anxiety of commitment. Therefore what\'s vital to finalize a workplace space? What factors are the deal breakers? Here are some thoughts.\"\r\n            </p>\r\n\r\n            <p>\r\n            <strong> <b>Location, location & location: -</b></strong> Indifferent of any industry, location is the utmost important factor which affects the bottom-line of the performance of the revenue. Workplace and a price-point that\'s right for you. You need to get into details of the gentry you are targeting & what consultation fee is trending. \r\n              </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            <strong> <b>Parking, parking, and additional parking.</b></strong> Offices measure parking corners. Between the professional (doctors/ lawyers/ teachers or yoga instructor) the employees and also the constant client flows, the automobile parking space will be overflowing in no time. Most sectionalisation laws need a parking magnitude relation of a minimum of four spots per number of workplace area, and generally additional with every thousand footage as per the local laws. More the parking slots better the flow of the patients coming in.\r\n              </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            <strong> <b>Existing Speciality offered :-</b></strong> Speciality offered in the space ranging from existing doctor or tutor practicing with number of years of experience they have shall directly impact the gentry of patients/students and number of footfall which are organically coming in the workplace.  \r\n              </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            <strong> <b> Avoid the evil :-</b></strong> Operations hassles shall not be ignored and belief of every professional should only worry about his practice rather than hassles of managing the day to day processes. You should analyse what sort of time and efforts it requires and what productive time it takes away from your day which should rather be utilized for actual consultancy.\r\n              </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n              Shop rigorously, take some time, take into account sharing a workplace area for effectiveness on Profrea.\r\n            </p>\r\n          </div>\r\n', 'Doctors', 'Pradeep', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2020-05-02 06:24:30', '2020-05-02 06:24:30'),
(3, 'Why Solo Entrepreneurs like doctors, teachers, lawyers & healthcare professionals need virtual reception services', '1.jpg', '\r\n			<div class=\"post-content color-text-a\">\r\n            <p class=\"post-intro\">\r\n            \"Virtual Reception Services: Solo Entrepreneur\'s Solution to Phone Answering. One of the top challenges solo service professionals face is managing limited resources. A small team is often responsible for a dizzying array of priorities on both the help in practicing and administrative sides of the business activities.\"             \r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n              One of the most common frustrations of a small private practice is simple: phone answering. Today, we\'re going to explore how virtual reception services can help resource-strapped firms serve existing and future clients with the type of customer service expected from big firms.\r\n              </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n              Hiring a virtual receptionist gives practitioner more time for billable consultation service\r\n              </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n              Virtual services, like phone answering, free up time for doctors and their team to work on serving clients. When you know the phones are being handled by a trained professional, you can work on other tasks without fear of being interrupted.\r\n              </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n              Your virtual receptionist will keep a log of callers and notes, including details on whether a return phone call is needed.\r\n              </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n              When you want to earn new clients, first impressions are everything\r\n              </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n              It\'s a Catch-22: Your practice needs to grow and acquire new clients. But, your day is already full of client\'s appointment, you simply don\'t have the time to stop for interruptions. No matter how much the call could help your practice to grow.\r\n              </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n              To make things even trickier two out of three potential clients say their decision to visit a workpace is primarily influenced by the firm\'s \"initial responsiveness\" as per the independent survey conducted by Profrea.\r\n              </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n              What\'s a busy professional do? The answer is simple: Show that your consultation is professional and responsive with a virtual receptionist service. You may even be able to find a professional who already has experience and training in your domain like healthcare etc. Many of our virtual assistants and receptionists are trained in client intake and other daily office intricacies, for example.\r\n              </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n              You\'ll never have to waste energy worrying about the phones again\r\n              </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n              With virtual reception help, you get peace of mind knowing the phones are under control. You don\'t have to worry about cell service in spotty coverage zones, and you\'ll never have to let people know you\'ll be unavailable during a plane ride or long deposition. Your receptionist will handle all incoming calls and can even assist with scheduling as needed.\r\n              </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n              If your workspace already has a receptionist, try conditional phone answering\r\n              </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n              During busy times of the year, do incoming calls sometimes get missed while your in-house receptionist is on another call? In these cases, it pays to have a conditional call forwarding service, where a receptionist will jump in to answer any calls that don\'t get answered after a few rings.\r\n              </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n              Conditional call forwarding is just one example of how flexible virtual reception solutions can be. To learn more about phone answering and other virtual assistant services for your private  practice, contact us on Profrea.com\r\n            <p>          \r\n            </div>\r\n\r\n', 'Doctors', 'Pradeep', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2020-05-02 06:24:30', '2020-05-02 06:24:30'),
(4, 'THINGS TO KEEP IN MIND FOR DESIGNING YOUR WORKSPACE', '1.jpg', '\r\n\r\n          <div class=\"post-content color-text-a\">\r\n            <p>\r\n            Technology redefining the equipment\'s as well as video call\'s to approach clients getting popular in India. Similarly, there are changes which needs to be implemented in the office space in itself.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p class=\"post-intro\">\r\n            We remember the time when clients would gobble up cabinets of professional, and a new office design for a solo professional would include a couple of exam rooms, a consultation room, and a small processing station. With the steep in property rent & a different approach these days. Now, the theme is consolidation and partnership with other practitioners, a hospital or institute, or integrated system so that providers can share space and disperse overhead costs for items such as new technology or additional staff to manage practice administration.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            If your budget is limited, don\'t despair. The beauty of undertaking a practice redesign or new build is that you can customize the scope and timeline of the project to suit your practice\'s individual needs. Here are some of the factors you\'ll need to consider before building your new space.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            <strong> <b> CHANGING NEEDS FOR SPACE</b></strong>\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            First priority being client\'s flow & staff efficiency and reassigning of new spaces that opened up. Clinic design and configuration has undergone significant changes over the years. There are several factors at play. The incorporation of new technology being the second priority among the factors to keep while designing the space.. Experts say these are some of the ways that practices are changing up their physical space:\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            <strong> <b>Professional\'s cubicle.</b></strong> Instead of a dedicated professional office, the OPD\'s have been shared with multiple professionals and freeing up real estate for more exam rooms. It works as a dedicated spot space to consult clients\' for the next steps.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            <strong> <b>Registration area for Clients.</b></strong> With dynamics changing clients privacy should be prioritise and seating area should be different offering more privacy for check-in, payment, and completion of the medical and social histories. Positive experience while waiting to be seen by the professionals should be the priority.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            <strong> <b>Exam rooms to be larger in size.</b></strong> Now that medicine has adopted a more consultative relationship between clients and professional, more clients are bringing a family member along to help them remember what the professional has to say and be an advocate. To accommodate three or even four people, exam rooms are increasing in size. \"You have to have a triangulation between the professional, the guest, and the clients. And the professionals needs to have access to the computer so he can be inputting all the pertinent information from interviewing the clients. Instead of initially exam rooms being 7-6 by 9-6; now it\'s preferred more like 11 by 9.\"\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            <strong> <b>Cloud-based IT solutions.</b></strong> Depending on the size of the practice and its technology choices and infrastructure, there may not be a server room or centralized computing centre with desktop computers, printers, fax machines, and scanners. If a practice chooses a cloud solution, they may only need a local area network (LAN) and devices with Wi-Fi capability, like laptops or tablets. But [also] facilities requirements like air conditioning for [the server] room, and the electricity needs.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            <strong> <b>CLIENTS FLOW</b></strong>\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            When the professional-owners decided that they needed to expand their centre to accommodate functions like in-house billing and administration, they chose to build a new facility, rather than redesign the old one.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            A well-designed practice has multiple benefits for both clients and staff, say experts. Eliminating traditional equipment which occupy rooms can open up space for things like multiple waiting rooms, consultation rooms, and separate check-in and check-out areas - all of which can improve clients flow and staff efficiency.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            A self-contained client\'s registration room, separate from the greeting area at the front desk. After clients have registered, they are moved to a second waiting room, big enough to accommodate family members or escorts for clients undergoing an out clients minor procedure.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            Not only does that facilitate clients flow, but it gives clients more privacy and a sense that they are being moved through the practice in a timely manner. Clients sitting in a crowded waiting room often wonder how long they will wait to be seen. \"Are not sure how many professionals are there. Are you one of 100 waiting for the same person? Or are there 10 professional\'s seeing all these clients?\" Eliminating the need to return to the front desk for check out has also been a desired design requirement.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            <strong> <b>CONSIDERING TECH NEEDS</b></strong>\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            There are very simple client\'s pleaser: for example, in-office Wi-Fi, made available to clients with a guest login, allows them to use personal mobile devices like smartphones and tablets while waiting for the professional.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            Client\'s registration tablets or kiosks allow clients to register, pay their copays and deductibles, complete social and medical histories, and even fill out short client\'s surveys at the conclusion of their visits. All without the additional work of transferring information from paper forms.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            <strong> <b>WHAT ARE THE NEXT STEPS</b></strong>\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            So what are the first steps once your practice has approved the plan for a new build/redesign? Well before approaching an architect, your practice should assemble focus groups in each department. Practice has a clear vision about what it wants and needs from a new space, and it is also important for staff members to voice their opinions on what doesn\'t work in the current environment. Everyone needs to be involved in the process. It\'s just not the provider input, it needs to come all the way down to the greeter.\r\n            </p>          \r\n            </div>\r\n\r\n', 'Doctors', 'Pradeep', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2020-05-02 06:24:30', '2020-05-02 06:24:30'),
(5, 'Solo Entrepreneur\'s Guide (Finally) Take Vacation', '1.jpg', '\r\n\r\n          <div class=\"post-content color-text-a\">\r\n            <p class=\"post-intro\">\r\n            \"How to Take Time off When You are a solo entrepreneur running our own clinic, coaching centre or healthcare workspaces\" \r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            If you\'re like most solo professionals having your own setup, you rarely (if ever) take an extended break from running your businesses. In fact, an independent surveys found that nearly only 50% of small business owners take major holidays off, if they take any time off at all. \r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            Even if you have a million things to do and the thought of disconnecting sends you into a panic, you need to relax and recharge. It might sound impossible, but virtually anyone can take time off if they plan ahead. Just use these tips to schedule guilt-free time away from your workspaces.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            <strong> <b>Advance Planning </b></strong>\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            Think about a typical year running your setup. You don\'t want to schedule vacation time during the busy season (say, monsoon) but there may be a slower period that could work out perfectly. Block out this time on your calendar as far in advance as you can manage.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            Once you\'ve selected dates, notify everyone who will need to know about your absence. Employees, client\'s, fellow professionals, and other people you work with regularly will all need to know. It\'s best to give a one month advance notice for longer absences, and one to two weeks for shorter vacations. Use your discretion - for example, you may want to give internal team members a head\'s up first.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            <strong> <b>Delegate </b></strong>\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            The setup won\'t fall apart while you\'re away, especially if you delegate properly.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            Think about all of your responsibilities, the clients you\'re working with, and everything else that you do in the practice. Then, look down the knowledge and skills needed to get the job done. If this person isn\'t yet on your team, don\'t worry, because you can always hire someone to help out. Profrea, helps you to list the requirements and get a professional from your very own industry. Browse, scrutinize the profile and choose the professional you like. So, say Dr Abhay who is a dermatologist wants a 15 days off. He can simply list his dates and timings than browse, scrutinize the profile and choose the dermatologist which he like and ask him to cover up for him.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            <strong> <b>Virtual assistants </b></strong>\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            Virtual assistants can be a great way to fill in gaps while you\'re out on vacation. They\'re capable of handling a wide variety of tasks, and you can use their services on an as-needed basis. Because you work with a virtual office services company (like Profrea), you don\'t even need to handle the nitty gritty of hiring and training. Virtual assistants already have basic business skills, and it\'s easy to train them on the specifics of what you need.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            Whether you delegate to a new person or someone who\'s already on your team, use it as an opportunity to document your processes and workflows in writing. Having a record of how things are done is invaluable and ensures that other people can step in to assist when needed. \r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            <strong> <b>Put in extra hours before your vacation </b></strong>\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            You may need to work harder than usual leading up to your vacation, and that\'s okay. Just make sure you have a plan and a solid understanding of everything that needs to get done before you leave. \r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            Equally important is knowing when you\'ll stop working and preparing. You may never feel 100% ready to take time off from your workspace, and that\'s normal. However, don\'t let your fears get in the way of doing what\'s best for your life and your setup. Everyone needs time off to recharge. You\'ll come back with a fresh mind that\'s motivated to tackle new challenges. \r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            Teams also need to know that their leader trusts they\'ll do a great job. With enough training and support, workers will be fully equipped to keep the practice running smoothly during your absence.\r\n            </p>    \r\n            </div>\r\n\r\n', 'Doctors', 'Pradeep', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2020-05-02 06:24:30', '2020-05-02 06:24:30'),
(6, 'Things to know before deciding your consultancy fee', '1.jpg', '\r\n\r\n          <div class=\"post-content color-text-a\">\r\n            <p class=\"post-intro\">\r\n            \"Pricing is one of the most difficult things you\'ll do as a private practitioner. If you set your price too high, you won\'t make enough number of consultations to make a profit. If the price is too low, you risk operating at a financial loss as well as client\'s not taking you seriously.\"            \r\n            </p>            \r\n            <p>\r\n            While there isn\'t a one-size-fits-all pricing strategy that will work for every profession/speciality, there are certain guidelines you can use to come to a price that makes sense for your setup and its clients. \r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            <strong> <b>What to consider when setting a fee </b></strong>\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            Regardless of the speciality you operate in, there are two key areas where you\'ll want to do some more in-depth research:\r\n            </p>\r\n            <ul>\r\n              <li> \r\n                Your target customers. Market research of your potential customers allows you to get to know the people you\'d ultimately like to sell to. You can research online (Practo, Lybrate etc. For doctors), send out email surveys to existing clients. Look into demographics, interests, income and other factors that might influence how much someone is willing to pay for your consultancy. \r\n              </li>\r\n              <li> \r\n                The competition. Competitive research is about more than seeing what professionals charge for similar consultancy. You also need to think about whether the extend of those consultancy are comparable to yours and how your offering stands out in a crowded marketplace, for example.in areas of Old Gurgaon if compared with areas in New Gurgaon the consultation fee shall vary a lot.    \r\n              </li>\r\n            </ul>            \r\n            <p>\r\n            <strong> <b>A simple strategy for pricing your project </b></strong>\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            Armed with some research-backed insights, you can get to work on the next part of consultancy pricing: choosing a number.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            There are countless pricing strategies that you can use to choose that number, but complicated isn\'t always better. To start, try this simple three step strategy for setting a consultancy fee:\r\n              </p>            \r\n            <ol>\r\n              <li> \r\n              Add up the variable costs per product. Totalling your variable costs can be easy or complex, depending on your practice area. If you practice in a office shared space your variable costs are relatively straightforward like spaces by Profrea. Professionals who are operating in their own setup they need to assess the costs of operations. Don\'t forget to include the cost of your time, too. \r\n              </li>\r\n              <li> \r\n              Add up your fixed costs per consultancy. Fixed costs are easier to calculate because they don\'t change from month-to-month. Rent is one example, because it will be the same regardless of how many consultations you do. \r\n              </li>\r\n              <li> \r\n              Determine a profit margin. You also need to make some money from consultancy. If you want say \"x\" % profit margin, for example, you can calculate a target price using this equation: Target Price = (Variable cost per product) / (1 - your desired profit margin as a decimal, which is 0.x in this case)\r\n              </li>\r\n            </ol>            \r\n            <p>\r\n            Once you have this price, don\'t forget to assess your fixed costs. Additionally, if the target price you calculate is sky-high compared to the competition, you\'ll need to go back to the drawing board.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            <strong> <b>Remember, the price you launch with isn\'t the price you\'re stuck with </b></strong>\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            Setting a price might sound like one of those decisions that\'s etched in stone forever once it\'s been made. This assumption couldn\'t be further from the truth, however.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            If the fee of your consultancy needs to change down the line, you are free to make the change. Some clients might be upset if the new price is higher, but you also need to make sure your pricing strategy allows you to turn a profit. \r\n            </p>\r\n          </div>\r\n', 'Doctors', 'Pradeep', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2020-05-02 06:24:30', '2020-05-02 06:24:30'),
(7, '5 Easy Money Saving Tips For Solo Solo Entrepreneurs Starting Their Practice', '1.jpg', '\r\n\r\n\r\n          <div class=\"post-content color-text-a\">\r\n             <b><h3>\r\n            How Practitioner Can Start Saving Money Today\r\n            </h3></b>\r\n            <br/><br/>\r\n            <p class=\"post-intro\">\r\n              \"The old saying, \"It takes money to make money\" might have some truth to it, but that doesn\'t mean your practice needs to burn through cash to become successful. There are plenty of ways private practitioner can save money, and here are 5 of the top tips.\" \r\n            </p>            \r\n\r\n            <strong> <b>1. Co-working office space</b></strong>\r\n            <p>\r\n              The most expensive expense of all is the right place to practice. There are multiple options to do that most expensive being the one where you open up your own clinic, coaching centre or healthcare space. The most smart & modern way is to share space with upfront tangible savings. Profrea empower you to do so.\r\n              </p>\r\n              <strong> <b>2. Eco-friendly methods for tech savvy millennials</b></strong>\r\n              <p>\r\n              When your business is green, it can be easier to save green. Go paperless, by sharing prescription/exam-papers etc. online as well. Use smart and eco-friendly ways to dispose of the wastes.\r\n              </p>\r\n              <strong> <b>3. Ditch the traditional lease for a shared satellite offices</b></strong>\r\n              <p>\r\n              If you currently have an office for your practice, you can save money by switching and opening up for shared office. Since shared spaces operate an an a-la-carte basis, you only rent out when you feel, and nothing more. That means you can rent out office space, by the hour, day, week, month or longer. The savings will be especially noticeable if you\'ve been locked into a traditional office lease.\r\n              </p>\r\n              <strong> <b>4. Save time to save money</b></strong>\r\n              <p>\r\n              Here\'s another old saying for you: Time is money. This one is all-too-true, because when you save time on certain tasks, you inevitably save money, too. \r\n              </p>\r\n              <p>\r\n              Use the handy advice in these articles to give yourself more freedom to focus on things that will help grow the business:\r\n              </p>\r\n              <strong> <b>5. Hire a Live Receptionist</b></strong>\r\n              <p>\r\n              Hiring someone might sound like the worst way to save money, but hear us out. As your consultancy grows, you need more people to help run things. Paying employee salaries and benefits can quickly add up. If you have an office, virtual or otherwise, you also need space for these team members to work. \r\n              </p>\r\n              <p>\r\n              Working with a virtual assistant is an ideal way to scale your company without hiring full-time staff. \r\n              </p>\r\n      \r\n          </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'Doctors', 'Pradeep', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2020-05-02 06:24:30', '2020-05-02 06:24:30'),
(8, 'Online Presence for Doctors: 6 Reasons Doctors Need It', '1.jpg', '\r\n\r\n\r\n          <div class=\"post-content color-text-a\">\r\n            <p>\r\n             Being connected online become an instant business benefit.\r\n            </p>\r\n             <b><h3>\r\n             Internet is a valuable tool for doctors.\r\n            </h3></b>\r\n            <br/><br/>\r\n            <p class=\"post-intro\">\r\n            \"Major platforms like LinkedIn, Facebook or homegrown communities such as Curofy are communities among others. As a doctor you want to ensure one thing, medium is less \"social\" and more \"business\" than Facebook\'s friends-and-family model. LinkedIn is older than the other \"big name\" social media platforms, and the business differentiation is a useful advantage for doctors, administrators, professionals and providers.\"\r\n            </p>            \r\n\r\n\r\n            <p>\r\n              The adoption curve has lagged a bit in the past, but its business and professional value remain strong. More than two million doctors and other practitioners maintain an individual or company profile.\r\n              </p>\r\n              <p>\r\n              For healthcare marketing purposes, LinkedIn\'s added value is that it is primarily for being visible among and connecting with fellow professionals. Here are some of the reasons that-more than ever-doctors need to be use LinkedIn:\r\n              </p>\r\n              <p>\r\n              <strong> <b>MANAGEMENT OF REPUTATION - </b></strong>To a great extent, a doctor\'s professional reputation lives and breathes online. Your online presence is the essence of your reputation. And what you say about yourself via LinkedIn is your digital reputation management tool. It is one platform and message that you directly control, direct and present the elements of your reputation and your personal brand.\r\n              </p>\r\n              <p>\r\n              <strong> <b>ENHANCED ONLINE VISIBILITY -</b></strong> Professional listings are authoritative and may carry added weight in the SEO process, so LinkedIn profiles can appear toward the top of search results page. In India Practo, Lybrate etc. leads due to the traction created in the market. The important distinction here is that you want to be found online and not just by new or prospective patients.\r\n              </p>\r\n              <p>\r\n              <strong> <b>YOU ARE YOUR PERSONAL BRAND - </b></strong>Your online presence is a showcase for your training, experience and achievements. Create a profile by definitely not being overly modest. Presenting your expertise and leadership is the need to emphasise while creating your personal profile. Your profile can be discovered by colleagues, hospital recruiters, as well as medical industry leaders.\r\n              </p>\r\n              <p>\r\n              <strong> <b>REFERRALS -</b></strong> Online enables doctor-to-doctor communications channel and pathway for referrals and professional networking. Anybody online is open to connections, networking and possibly, professional referrals.\r\n              </p>\r\n              <p>\r\n              <strong> <b>CAREER ADVANCEMENT -</b></strong>Being connected-or linked-is the first step in being known for healthcare employers and prospective employees. Staffing and recruiting is a process of seeing and being seen online. Your online presence makes you stand out for career advancement opportunities\r\n              </p>\r\n              <p>\r\n              <strong> <b>CONTINUING EDUCATION -</b></strong> Both learn and to teach are enabled through online these days. Articles can relate to virtually any appropriate subject and keep readers in touch with timely topic, news or trend. It is also a window to track thought leaders, hospitals and organization even fellow doctors.\r\n              </p>\r\n              <p>\r\n              Virtually for every professional and professional practice, online is a mandatory marketing- and reputation-smart tool for healthcare and business.\r\n            </p>\r\n          </div>\r\n\r\n', 'Doctors', 'Pradeep', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2020-05-02 06:24:30', '2020-05-02 06:24:30'),
(9, 'Importance of Satellite Medical Work office', '1.jpg', '\r\n          <div class=\"post-content color-text-a\">\r\n            <p class=\"post-intro\">\r\n            Extend your practice with Satellite work office. It\'s not a place where you dedicate your whole day but ensure you serve that part of the city. Enabling you to get the best experience without financially burden and long commitments.\r\n            </p>          \r\n\r\n            <p>\r\n            Satellite office is an ideal match for whom? \r\n            </p>\r\n              <p>\r\n              <strong> <b>Beginners :- </b></strong>If you\'re simply just beginning your practice, you don\'t need to overstrain yourself financially trying  to get access to an expert medical workplace space. Begin with simply a day or 2 per week and grow to additional days as your observe grows. Keep adaptable as you\'re not stuck into long leases. If you\'re experienced however wanting to grow your practice you can opt for a longer time slots in your satellite office itself. \r\n            </p>\r\n              <p>\r\n            <strong> <b>Seasoned practitioners :-  </b></strong>Are you at a stage in your life where you want to simplify and scale down, but not shut down and retire.  With our range of listings of medical office sharing spaces, you can scale down just as easily as you can scale up.  Go from 5 days a week to 4 to 3 to 2 as you free up your time to pursue other interests without feeling like you have to run at either 100% or 0% just so you can feed the machine of the big medical office and staff.\r\n            </p>\r\n              <p>\r\n              <strong> <b>Practitioner who want to test the market-- </b></strong>increase the population you serve. Do you have a practice in Old Gurgaon and want to expand into New Gurgaon?  Rather than make a multi-year commitment and embark upon an expensive build out, try one day a week at Golf Course road or Sohna Road.  You may find that there is more demand than you expected, but if not, you won\'t be locked into a long-term contract.\r\n            </p>\r\n              <p>\r\n              <strong> <b>Pay only for the days you need :- </b></strong> If you practice in New Gurgaon only one or two days per week, you pay for only those days.  Your patients see your name on the directory and on the door, and know the right time when to reach back to you.\r\n            </p>\r\n              <p>\r\n              <strong> <b>On-call availability :- </b></strong> You pay for only those days when you practice. If, you want to make yourself available on call. Profrea connects you to multiple clinics, patients see your name on the directory and can get in touch with you. Clinics also can give a shout-out if they need you in case for a patient who needs your expertise.\r\n            </p>\r\n              <p>\r\n            We don\'t get involved in your business at all. We are not a wellness center trying to build our own practice. We are purely a specialized medical workspace service provider designed specifically to serve the unique needs of many of today\'s medical and wellness practitioners.\r\n            </p>\r\n              <p>\r\n            Signing a 5+ year lease, for space than you really want, signing a personal guarantee, and putting up a hefty security deposit, and often spending lots of money on configuring the space to your needs, furnishing it and decorating it. Then if your needs change, you\'re stuck in a long-term lease. Satellite  office is an easy answer which saves you from a lot of problem and ensure in helping out to extend your practice.\r\n            </p>\r\n\r\n          </div>\r\n\r\n', 'Doctors', 'Pradeep', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2020-05-02 06:24:30', '2020-05-02 06:24:30'),
(10, 'SHOULD I BE A DOCPRENEUR?', '1.jpg', '\r\n\r\n <div class=\"post-content color-text-a\">\r\n            <p class=\"post-intro\">\r\n              \"Should I own my own clinic, I guarantee that by the end of these 5 minutes you\'ll have a really good idea if you should own your own clinic or continue to work for someone else. We\'ll be going over the pros and cons of owning your own clinic and this all started from a question our clinic consultants get almost every day. Should I start my private practice?\"\r\n            </p>          \r\n\r\n            <p>\r\n\r\n              I have been a practicing Internal Medicine for 2 years I started working for a large Hospital chain and took the plunge into owning my own clinic so I have done both, worked for someone else and started my own successful clinic giving me the experience of both sides of employment.\r\n              </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n              I can really see the benefits and disadvantages of both but I have to say I\'m really happy I decided to open my own clinic I\'m excited to share my insights with all of the medical fraternity today. I have identified three personality traits that can predict whether you have the potential to be a successful clinic owner & also explain how those personality traits can be used to answer the following two questions and they are \r\n              </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n              1) Am I ready to be my own boss?\r\n              </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n              2) Do I have a plan for my success? \r\n              </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n              Let\'s start with that first question am I ready to be my own boss it seems like a simple question right who doesn\'t want to be their own boss. It\'s great you get to be in complete control you get to put your own business ideas into practice and most importantly you can create an environment that you enjoy going to every day for sure I mean those are amazing positives do you think people ever get blind by the positive aspects of owning their own business yeah I think it\'s easy to focus on the positives like flexible hours and better work/life balance and forget the nitty gritty of being a small business owner. \r\n              </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n              I think it\'s important for readers to remember that they become a small business owner as well as a treating clinician if they choose to open their own clinic it can be challenging for a health care professional to understand that their practices also their business you really have to be honest with yourself determine how entrepreneurial you really are and consider all aspects involved with owning a practice so when you ask yourself am I ready to be my own boss what exactly does that entail you might be ready mentally to be your own boss but you have to prepare for it to make sure you have the skills they need to succeed have you considered what kind of clinic you\'d like to run how you structure the business from the legal standpoint are you prepared to oversee the bookkeeping and accounting are you familiar with the laws and all regulations do you have management and operations experience have you thought about your own company policies operations and procedures wow that\'s a lot and when you work as an employee you don\'t really have to worry about all of those things all at once absolutely it\'s easy to get discouraged from starting your own clinic when you don\'t feel like you have enough experience or don\'t immediately know the answer to one of those questions true I think most people would agree it takes a really specific personality type to be successful and the best bosses are persistent I think as healthcare professionals we all have it in us we have the people\'s skills required to manage and lead a team we\'re also trained to be methodical by evaluating a patient\'s injury objectively and finding a solution it\'s therefore ingrained in us to be a results-driven which I found carried over well to the business side of things that\'s really interesting but if someone isn\'t naturally persistent should they always work for someone else the fact that you are reading this and you are interested in becoming your own boss means you\'re already starting to demonstrate that personality trait. \r\n              </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n              How being persistent helps prepare you to become your own boss you don\'t necessarily have to be an expert in all aspects of your business you have to be honest with yourself and about your own professional limitations and resilient enough to find the solution can you give a real-life example of that is accounting is critical to operating a successful business but I don\'t necessarily have to be a bookkeeper in order to succeed however I do need to spend the time to find the right person or a company to take on that task. \r\n              </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n              So being your own boss doesn\'t mean doing everything yourself absolutely not to me being a good boss is understanding what business as a whole and allocating resources appropriately I physically can\'t do everything and know everything what I can do is dedicate the time to finding the right people and guide them to be sure that the right work gets done. \r\n              </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n              Speaking of the overall vision that brings us to the next question you should be asking yourself do I have a plan for my success before sitting down and coming up with a plan you should define what success looks like for you it will be different for every person and depending on what you want your outcome to be it\'ll influence your business plan. \r\n              </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n              We\'ve mentioned a few already but what are some of the reasons that someone would want to open a clinic there are lots of reasons but the three main reasons I\'ve seen our profitability offering your own clinic while treating means there\'s no limit on your success the harder you work the more you can earn flexibility you can control your own work-life balance three professional growth you know the industry and want to take on more maybe move into more of a managerial role regardless of your motive you need to keep in mind the primary reason you\'re deciding to open up your own clinic when you come up with a business plan \r\n              </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n              What motivates you as an individual, your primary goal should be what gets you up in the morning it\'s what you\'re really passionate about it\'s a from my own experience most clinicians are very passionate of giving quality patient care successful businesspeople are passionate about becoming profitable and clinicals need to be a hybrid of both.\r\n              </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n              Some clinicians see their income double when they become clinic owners it\'s true but success can never be guaranteed you really do need to plan and that can be broken down to three parts before during and after opening your clinic let\'s talk a bit about that what should you do before opening the clinic.\r\n              </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n              As a healthcare professional there should be outreach of your skill in the community. To get that proper outreach in the community instead of putting in investment or hassles of operations in your own clinic. To begin your Docpreneur journey you can rent out or share a clinic with the healthcare professionals. \r\n              </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n              You need to work on basic four things to do that, first find a location where you want to practice, second legal paperwork for the arrangement with the healthcare facility, third phone-line arrangement where you don\'t need to attend all the calls, fourth and last get your business cards. Going through these all arrangements is a headache & as a medicine practitioner myself I understand the pain.  \r\n              </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n              Profrea get you covered in all these it\'s a unique plug & play platform where you can browse multiple clinic options listed as per the location. Look for a clinic you prefer either it can be near to your Hospital or your home. It gets you covered with all legal rental arrangement in a jiffy. Profrea has a unique offering where you can get your virtual real coordinator in one-fourth of the price. It\'s real people with real offerings, who don\'t only attend your calls they do the follow up\'s with patient\'s, give you reminders & maintain your calendar & basically make your life easy & save you a lot of time. Last but not the least Profrea offer you a professional complimentary kit of marketing tools which get you covered starting with your own Business cards, prescription pads etc. So, forget all the hassles and begin your Docpreneur journey.\r\n            </p>\r\n    \r\n            <strong><b><u> Author </u></b></strong><br/>\r\n            Dr. L.Chatterjee<br/>\r\n            <b><u> [MD (Medicine, MBBS, FID, FAM] </u></b>\r\n\r\n          </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'Doctors', 'Dr. L.Chatterjee', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2020-05-02 06:24:30', '2020-05-02 06:24:30');
INSERT INTO `faq` (`id`, `question`, `answer`, `category`, `rowstate`, `insert`, `update`) VALUES
(1, 'What is profrea?', 'Profrea is a revolutionary platform where workspace seekers will find workspaces on hourly basis. Pay for what you use, instead paying hefty rent.', 'General', 1, '2020-05-02 06:24:30', '2020-05-02 06:24:30'),
(2, 'Who can list workspace?', 'Anyone who owns a workspace or who is a lessee or who has the power to license the workspace to any third party. Anyone who lists the workspace shall be called as Space Provider.', 'General', 1, '2020-05-02 06:24:30', '2020-05-02 06:24:30'),
(3, 'Who can book my listed workspace?', 'Anyone who completes the requirements of the listed workspace may book the workspace on hourly license basis. Anyone who books a workspace shall be called as Space User.', 'General', 1, '2020-05-02 06:24:30', '2020-05-02 06:24:30'),
(4, 'Is it renting of a workspace?', 'No, it\'s not a rent, lease or sublease. It is only a license to occupy and use workspace.', 'General', 1, '2020-05-02 06:24:30', '2020-05-02 06:24:30'),
(5, 'What will be the arrangement?', 'It\'s a simple standard two page Space License Agreement executed between the Space Provider and the Space User on agreed terms and conditions.', 'General', 1, '2020-05-02 06:24:30', '2020-05-02 06:24:30'),
(6, 'How is workspace priced?', 'Workspace is priced by the Space Provider on hourly basis. The listed price of the workspace shall include license fee, electricity charges, water charges, property tax, etc. Space Provider has the option of listing paid utilities separately and price for the same shall be mentioned in Space License Agreement.', 'General', 1, '2020-05-02 06:24:30', '2020-05-02 06:24:30'),
(7, 'What is Profrea\'s fee?', 'Workspace listing by space provider is totally free. \"Real Easy Estate LLP\" i.e. owner of \"www.profrea.com\" charges 15 days license fee of aggregate Space License Fee charged by Space Provider from the Space User. Space User\'s are charged ZERO service fee throughout.', 'General', 1, '2020-05-02 06:24:30', '2020-05-02 06:24:30'),
(8, 'What is the tenure of the Space License Agreement?', 'Tenure of the agreement is for 3 months or 6 months.', 'General', 1, '2020-05-02 06:24:30', '2020-05-02 06:24:30'),
(9, 'Can i ask for security deposit?', 'Yes, space provider can ask for security deposit from the Space User which is a typical one month security.', 'Space Provider', 1, '2020-05-02 06:24:30', '2020-05-02 06:24:30'),
(10, 'Can I list my workspace if I am a tenant?', 'Yes, you simply need to get a NOC from your lessor. Contact us to get a free template.', 'Space Provider', 1, '2020-05-02 06:24:30', '2020-05-02 06:24:30'),
(11, 'What are pre-requisite to list my workspace?', 'All you need is a vacant/idle workspace for minimum 2 hours in a day and a workspace manager.', 'Space Provider', 1, '2020-05-02 06:24:30', '2020-05-02 06:24:30'),
(12, 'Can I define a criteria for Space User I want to list for?', 'Yes absolutely. You shall mention pre-qualifications of the Space User you want to list for at the time of listing your workspace. Moreover, Space Provider has the right to reject or accept the Space User before the execution of Space License Agreement.', 'Space Provider', 1, '2020-05-02 06:24:30', '2020-05-02 06:24:30'),
(13, 'Can I ask for additional information about the Space User?', 'Yes absolutely. You shall forward the questions or queries to \"Profrea\", who shall thereby forward it to Space User. You shall be forwarded the answers and the documents as provided by Space User.', 'Space Provider', 1, '2020-05-02 06:24:30', '2020-05-02 06:24:30'),
(14, 'How can I get specific questions answered on a particular workspace?', 'Feel free to contact us for more details.', 'Space User', 1, '2020-05-02 06:24:30', '2020-05-02 06:24:30'),
(15, 'Can I schedule a visit to a workspace listed on the platform?', 'Yes, we will arrange a visit to the selected workspace on pittance charges.', 'Space User', 1, '2020-05-02 06:24:30', '2020-05-02 06:24:30');
